snippet.textDisplay: I remember I had this school that was junior high and highschool altogether, just on a different campus, but we used the same cafeteria. A few years before I attended. Some seniors that got expelled because of violence, snuck in the café and trashed it, I don't know how it looked like but one of my friends' elder siblings used to go there and apparently there was wet toilet paper, cheese, yoghurt, gum and rotten fruit all over the place, they were able to clean it up but some of remained on the ceiling and it stayed like that for a few years, 5-6 years later I'm 13 and I get transfered there, I was in the cafeteria with my older brother who especially came from the other campus to show me around. Then we heard a huge SPLUSH and girls screaming we turned around to see one of the juniors soaking wet with tomato soup all over her and her friends, her friends reached out to her to comfort her, whatever it was on the ceiling dropped into her soup bowl, (spinach, it was 5 year old spinach) suddenly other things started falling from the ceiling, people were screaming and some laughing, it was beautifully gnarly, everyone had to get out and the poor victims who had something on them were sent home.
